Evacuations have started in Bloemhof in the North West, amid fears of flooding due to heavy rains. Some residents have already moved to a local hall. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Evacuations have started in Bloemhof in the North West amid fears of flooding due to heavy rains. Some residents have already moved to a local hall. READ: Flood-hit Ladysmith braces for more rain Meanwhile, in Ladysmith, KwaZulu-Natal,  business owners, and residents have started counting the costs after devastating floods. About 150 people have been affected by the worst floods in the town's recent history.